C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66db3264a0ff598b26655aef%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221737%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20and%20her%20friends%20jokingly%20called%20themselves%20%26quot%3BThe%20Commune%26quot%3B%20because%20they%20did%20everything%20together.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fsex-relationships%2Frough-patch-in-relationship%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebonded%20over%20shared%20interests%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20developed%20new%20ones%20together.%20During%20the%20worst%20parts%20of%20COVID-19%2C%20our%20weeks%20consisted%20of%20us%20spending%20between%20three%20to%20five%20nights%20a%20week%20together%20with%20activities%20ranging%20from%20cooking%20dinner%2C%20casual%20wine%20nights%20with%20games%2C%20poolside%20hangouts%2C%20walks%2C%20and%20%E2%80%94%20when%20allowed%20%E2%80%94%20the%20occasional%20evening%20dining%20out.%20Not%20to%20mention%20overnight%20trips%20to%20Montreal%20for%20the%20girls%20and%20the%20occasional%20%26quot%3Bfamily%26quot%3B%20vacation%20to%20a%20cottage%20or%20wine%20country.%20For%20those%20of%20us%20who%20weren't%20parents%20to%20the%20baby%2C%20we%20treated%20him%20as%20our%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ecfb3ac9-b656-42d8-88f7-9c4d07b9c94d%5C%22%3EWe%20call%20ourselves%20'The%20Commune'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20talked%20about%20opening%20a%20wine%20bar%20and%20buying%20a%20shared%20cottage%20and%20lamented%20how%20things%20would%20be%20easier%20if%20we%20had%20a%20massive%20compound.%20We%20called%20ourselves%20%26quot%3BThe%20Commune.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20this%20time%2C%20the%20couple%20that%20was%20not%20yet%20married%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fengagement-ring-shopping-together-before-proposal-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egot%20engaged%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20then%20wed.%20We%20were%20all%20there%20celebrating%20our%20family%20that%20was%20not%20exactly%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20just%20over%20a%20year%20later%2C%20I%20got%20a%20text%2C%20%26quot%3BBrian%20and%20I%20are%20separating.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20at%20my%20office%20when%20the%20text%20came%20in%2C%20and%20my%20stomach%20dropped.%20My%20immediate%20response%20was%20to%20tend%20to%20the%20needs%20of%20my%20friend%2C%20ensuring%20that%20she%20was%20OK%20and%20offering%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Femotional-support-dog%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemotional%20support%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20reality%2C%20my%20hands%20started%20shaking%2C%20and%20tears%20pricked%20at%20the%20corners%20of%20my%20eyes.%20I%20was%20sick%20to%20my%20stomach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20got%20home%20from%20work%2C%20and%20for%20a%20few%20days%20following%2C%20I%20let%20myself%20cry%2C%20sometimes%20uncontrollably.%20I%20understood%20and%20supported%20the%20reasons%20for%20the%20separation%20%E2%80%94%20people%20deserve%20to%20be%20happy.%20But%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20I%20knew%20that%20things%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20us%20would%20never%20be%20the%20same%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20break%20up%20was%20also%20ours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2280872caa-f2c6-45fc-8fef-feeb8eec9abe%5C%22%3EA%20clean%20split%20was%20impossible%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETypically%2C%20the%20lines%20in%20a%20group%20of%20friends%20tend%20to%20be%20clearer%20to%20allow%20for%20a%20cleaner%2C%20less%20painful%20split%2C%20where%20the%20friends%20you%20bring%20into%20a%20relationship%20are%20the%20ones%20you%20leave%20with.%20In%20this%20situation%2C%20we%20were%20so%20deeply%20enmeshed%20in%20each%20other's%20lives%20that%20a%20clean%20split%20was%20impossible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20emotional%20labor%20has%20been%20put%20on%20the%20parties%20not%20involved%20to%20navigate%20social%20events.%20We%20try%20to%20ensure%20that%20no%20tears%20are%20shed%20on%20birthdays%2C%20and%20to%20make%20sure%20everyone%20feels%20included%20and%20supported.%20This%20gets%20thornier%20as%20our%20friends%20venture%20into%20dating%2C%20and%20we%20need%20to%20accommodate%20the%20feelings%20of%20other%20new%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20year%20since%20the%20separation%2C%20the%20dust%20has%20begun%20to%20settle%2C%20and%20the%20relationship%20dynamics%20are%20calcifying%2C%20thanks%2C%20in%20large%20part%2C%20to%20self-selection.%20As%20with%20any%20breakup%2C%20things%20get%20easier%20with%20time%3B%20I%20never%20expected%20to%20experience%20those%20same%20feelings%20about%20someone%20else's%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20time%20we%20were%20all%20together%20before%20the%20separation%20was%20a%20weekday%20in%20September%20%E2%80%94%20mere%20weeks%20before%20the%20break%20up%20%E2%80%94%20enjoying%20the%20last%20few%20days%20warm%20enough%20to%20sit%20around%20the%20edge%20of%20the%20pool%2C%20dangling%20our%20feet%20into%20the%20cool%20water.%20We%20drank%20wine%20and%20talked%20about%20the%20summer%2C%20about%20the%20things%20we%20had%20coming%20up%20over%20the%20next%20few%20weeks.%20We%20joked%20around%20in%20the%20ways%20family%20does.%20Things%20were%20normal.%20The%20couple%20with%20the%20child%20were%20heading%20on%20vacation%20and%20we%20were%20to%20see%20them%20upon%20their%20return.%20But%20that%20never%20happened.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20little%20regard%20we%20have%20for%20the%20mundane%20interactions%20with%20those%20we%20love.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20mourn%20the%20end%20of%20romantic%20relationships%20and%2C%20increasingly%2C%20the%20end%20of%20friendships.%20But%20how%20do%20you%20mourn%20the%20end%20of%20a%20relationship%20you%20were%20never%20in%20in%20the%20first%20place%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffriends-broke-up-relationship-tore-group-friend-apart-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3