r%20experiences%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Rossman%20said%2C%20pointing%20to%20success%20among%20airlines%20and%20travel-oriented%20firms.%20However%2C%20they%20seem%20to%20have%20tired%20out%20on%20goods.%20Around%2040%25%20of%20consumers%20said%20they%20planned%20to%20pare%20back%20spending%20on%20accessories%2C%20home%20decor%2C%20jewelry%2C%20and%20furniture%2C%20per%20McKinsey's%20survey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20like%2C%20people%20are%20going%20to%20spend%2C%20but%20they're%20only%20going%20to%20spend%20when%20they%20feel%20like%20there's%20really%20value%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20Rossman%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECustomers%20have%20likely%20refined%20their%20spending%20habits%2C%20with%20more%20Americans%20now%20searching%20for%20high-quality%20products%20at%20a%20good%20value%2C%20according%20to%20Simeon%20Siegel%2C%20a%20senior%20retail%20and%20ecommerce%20analyst%20at%20BMO.%20That's%20why%20firms%20at%20the%20low-end%20%E2%80%94%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmcdonalds-expensive-prices-too-high-fast-food-restaurant-falling-sales-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMcDonald's%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20as%20well%20as%20on%20the%20high-end%20%E2%80%94%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstarbucks-lvmh-loreal-declining-sales-china-earnings-consumer-luxury-retail-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELVMH%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20are%20struggling%2C%20he%20said.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20many%20retailers%20that%20saw%20an%20across-the-board%20boom%20in%20profits%20amid%20post-pandemic%20revenge%20shopping%2C%20it's%20the%20end%20of%20an%20era%2C%20and%20companies%20are%20scrambling%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20navigate%20the%20new%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.challengergray.com%2Fblog%2Fcnbc-retail-ceo-turnover-soars-and-fewer-women-hold-top-jobs-in-the-industry%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECEO%20turnover%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20retail%20industry%20more%20than%20doubled%20last%20year%2C%20with%20the%20sector%20notching%20the%20highest%20number%20of%20CEO%20change-ups%20in%20four%20years%2C%20according%20to%20Challenger%2C%20Gray%20%26amp%3B%20Christmas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20firms%20are%20also%20on%20high-alert%20for%20how%20consumers%20are%20reacting%20to%20higher%20prices.%2086%25%20of%20consumer%20staples%20firms%20in%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20mentioned%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finsight.factset.com%2Ffewer-sp-500-companies-discussing-inflation-on-earnings-calls-for-7th-straight-quarter%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einflation%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20in%20their%20first%20quarter%20earnings%20call%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20FactSet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20retailers%2C%20like%20Walmart%20and%20Target%2C%20have%20turned%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstores-cutting-prices-summer-list-walmart-target-amazon-aldi-walgreens-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaggressively%20slashing%20prices%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20a%20sign%20that%20stores%20are%20getting%20more%20desperate%20in%20their%20efforts%20to%20get%20shoppers%20in%20the%20door%2C%20Siegel%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20the%20consumer%20had%20a%20wallet%20full%20of%20cash%20handed%20to%20them%2C%20they%20didn't%20have%20to%20be%20as%20thoughtful.%20They%20didn't%20have%20to%20hold%20back.%20And%20so%20everyone%20benefited.%20We're%20now%20back%20in%20an%20environment%20where%20good%20retailers%2C%20strong%20brands%20that%20offer%20compelling%20value%20%E2%80%A6%20will%20benefit%2C%26quot%3B%20Siegel%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222d50d303-346d-40f3-83e6-620eeca3d56c%5C%22%3EPicky%20shoppers%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20stark%20turnaround%20from%20several%20years%20ago%2C%20when%20Americans%20under%20stay-at-home%20orders%20and%20flush%20with%20stimulus%20cash%20were%20buying%20just%20about%20everything.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20those%20consumers%20have%20largely%20spent%20down%20their%20pile%20of%20extra%20cash%2C%20with%20household%20excess%20savings%20likely%20having%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.frbsf.org%2Fresearch-and-insights%2Fblog%2Fsf-fed-blog%2F2024%2F05%2F03%2Fpandemic-savings-are-gone-whats-next-for-us-consumers%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DWe%2520estimate%2520that%2520excess%2520savings%2Cover%2520the%2520subsequent%25202%25C2%25BD%2520years.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edepleted%20by%20the%20first%20quarter%20of%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20a%20projection%20from%20the%20San%20Francisco%20Fed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20consumers%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20those%20in%20the%20lower-%20to%20middle-income%20bracket%20%E2%80%94%20are%20showing%20signs%20that%20they're%20having%20trouble%20dealing%20with%20the%20higher%20cost%20of%20living.%20Less%20than%20half%20of%20middle-class%20Americans%20rated%20their%20personal%20finances%20as%20%26quot%3Bexcellent%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bgood%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20two-thirds%20of%20middle-class%20Americans%20said%20they%20believed%20their%20income%20was%20falling%20behind%20the%20cost%20of%20living%2C%20according%20to%20a%20second-quarter%20survey%20conducted%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.primerica.com%2Fpublic%2FFact_Sheet_Primerica_Financial_Security_Monitor_Q2_2024.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPrimerica%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInflation%20has%20cooled%20from%20its%20highs%20several%20years%20ago%2C%20but%20the%20increased%20selectiveness%20among%20consumers%20will%20likely%20continue%20for%20the%20foreseeable%20future%2C%20Rossman%20and%20Siegel%20predicted%2C%20due%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20it%20takes%20time%20for%20people's%20perception%20of%20the%20economy%20to%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20could%20correctly%20say%2C%20oh%2C%20inflation's%20come%20way%20down%2C%20but%20people's%20rents%20are%20up%2C%20people's%20grocery%20bills%20are%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20Rossman%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20going%20to%20take%20a%20while%20to%20unwind%20some%20of%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20meantime%2C%20that%20could%20mean%20more%20pain%20for%20retailers%2C%20Siegel%20said%2C%20speculating%20that%20many%20were%20caught%20by%20surprise%20by%20the%20shift%20in%20consumer%20sentiment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInvestors%20are%20already%20feeling%20uneasy.%20Retail%20stocks%20are%20struggling%2C%20with%20SPDR%20S%26amp%3BP%20retail%20exchange-traded%20fund%20falling%20more%20than%205%25%20over%20the%20past%20six%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCompanies%20either%20had%20product%20or%20they%20didn't%2C%20consumers%20either%20had%20stimulus%20or%20they%20didn't%2C%26quot%3B%20Siegel%20said%20of%20pandemic%20times%2C%20noting%20that%20most%20retailers%20were%20able%20to%20succeed%20during%20the%20pandemic%20so%20long%20as%20they%20had%20inventory%20hitting%20the%20shelves.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20we're%20back%20to%20an%20environment%20where%20there%20are%20winners%20or%20losers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20weakest%20or%20most%20indebted%20retailers%20out%20there%2C%20it%20could%20mean%20that%20their%20businesses%20will%20continue%20to%20shrink%2C%20Siegel%20said%2C%20though%20he%20noted%20he%20wasn't%20necessarily%20predicting%20a%20wave%20of%20company%20failures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20that%20the%20businesses%2C%20the%20management%20teams%20that%20plan%20only%20for%20good%20times%20are%20the%20management%20teams%20that%20won't%20be%20around%20for%20very%20long%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretail-consumers-spending-shopping-economy-covid-stimulus-inflation-xrt-etf-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725797762000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66db2371a0ff598b266548a5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.co