ance%20productivity%20and%20employee%20well-being%20to%20retain%20talent.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAmericans%20are%20well-known%20for%20being%20hard%20workers.%20The%20midday%20siestas%20and%20monthlong%20vacations%20so%20beloved%20in%20Europe%20don't%20cut%20it%20with%20bosses%20stateside.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Febs%2Flatest-numbers.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20nearly%20one%20in%20four%20US%20workers%20isn't%20entitled%20to%20a%20paid%20sick%20day.%20But%20despite%20their%20industrious%20reputation%2C%20there%20is%20evidence%20that%20the%20predominantly%20white-collar%20Americans%20who%20do%20receive%20PTO%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-sick-leave-pto-mental-health-work-from-home-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eare%20taking%20more%20sick%20leave%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20ever%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHR%20platforms%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-sick-leave-pto-mental-health-work-from-home-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDayforce%20and%20Gusto%2C%20for%20example%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20both%20reported%20a%20jump%20in%20the%20amount%20of%20sick%20leave%20people%20are%20taking%2C%20based%20on%20companies%20they%20surveyed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pandemic%20changed%20workers'%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpaid-sick-leave-coronavirus-states-barred-local-governments-prevent-spread-2020-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eattitudes%20to%20sick%20leave%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20raising%20awareness%20about%20the%20importance%20of%20staying%20home%20to%20avoid%20infecting%20coworkers%20and%20the%20need%20to%20care%20for%20mental%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20human%20resources%20experts%20also%20say%20there's%20another%20major%20shift%20affecting%20attitudes%20to%20sick%20leave%3A%20the%20arrival%20of%20Gen%20Z%20in%20the%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERue%20Dooley%2C%20HR%20knowledge%20advisor%20at%20the%20Society%20for%20Human%20Resource%20Management%20and%20a%20Gen%20Xer%2C%20said%20that%20his%20generation%20had%20been%20socialized%20and%20conditioned%20for%20decades%20to%20think%20that%20the%20more%20you%20work%2C%20the%20better%20you%20are%20as%20a%20human.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20behavior%20doesn't%20change%20overnight%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dooley.%20%26quot%3BBut%20Gen%20Z%20has%20a%20different%20way%20of%20thinking%20and%20communicating.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Low%20angle%20view%20of%20three%20people%20using%20their%20mobiles.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6628f6490dfb1341e9fe5899%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EExperts%20say%20Gen%20Z%20is%20demanding%20better%20work-life%20balance.%3Cp%3EXavier%20Lorenzo%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20young%20workers%20Dooley%20speaks%20to%20feel%20entitled%20to%20sick%20leave%20as%20if%20it's%20a%20cultural%20norm.%20Their%20ideas%20are%20having%20an%20impact%20because%20the%20generational%20differences%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ebetween%20Gen%20Z%20and%20millennials%20are%20far%20greater%20than%20they%20usually%20are%20between%20generations%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYounger%20workers%20are%20behaving%20in%20such%20a%20way%20that%20it%20is%20an%20entitlement.%20I%20should%20get%20time%20off%20when%20I%20need%20it%20without%20having%20to%20get%20special%20permission%20or%20feeling%20judged%20or%20condemned.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EImproved%20technology%20and%20connectivity%20also%20make%20their%20demands%20more%20feasible%20%E2%80%94%20they%20can%20be%20online%20anywhere%20and%20anytime.%20The%20downside%20is%20that%20the%20boundaries%20around%20work%20are%20blurring%2C%20Dooley%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20if%20you%20are%20strategic%2C%20conscientious%2C%20and%20you%20have%20access%2C%20you%20can%20be%20much%20more%20efficient%2C%20and%20you%20can%20have%20this%20work-life%20balance%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20And%20if%20employers%20don't%20give%20in%20to%20it%2C%20the%20labor%20market%20won't%20respond%20favorably%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e338b862-99e2-4a45-adaa-3f2b3cda997d%5C%22%3EPressure%20to%20keep%20working%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20UK%2C%20where%20legislation%20has%20entitled%20all%20workers%20to%20sick%20pay%20since%201983%2C%20the%20issue%20of%20sick%20leave%20isn't%20as%20pertinent.%20But%20that%20doesn't%20mean%20it's%20not%20changed%20since%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20data%20shows%20that%20the%20Brits%20are%20taking%20more%20time%20off%20%E2%80%94%20the%20average%20number%20of%20days%20British%20workers%20took%20off%20for%20sick%20leave%20increased%20from%205.8%20days%20in%202019%20to%207.8%20days%20in%202023%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eaccording%20to%20UK-based%20HR%20body%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cipd.org%2Fuk%2Fviews-and-insights%2Fthought-leadership%2Fcipd-voice%2Fsickness-absence-rate-jumps%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChartered%20Institute%20of%20Personnel%20and%20Development%3C%2Fa%3E%20(CIPD).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Cary%20Cooper%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20organizational%20psychology%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Manchester%20in%20the%20UK%20said%20the%20numbers%20don't%20reflect%20the%20full%20picture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20because%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fresenteeism-quiet-quitting-recession-jobs-inflation-labor-shortage-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epresenteeism%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20employees%20log%20on%20but%20cannot%20function%20well%2C%20is%20also%20increasing%2C%20said%20Cooper%2C%20recently%20president%20of%20the%20CIPD.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20that%20abuse%20the%20system%20are%20very%20small%2C%20and%20with%20jobs%20so%20insecure%20at%20the%20moment%2C%20they%20want%20to%20work%20and%20deliver%20for%20their%20bosses%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Cooper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHybrid%20workers%20feel%20pressure%20to%20be%20seen%20as%20reliable.%20So%2C%20where%20a%20common%20cold%20may%20have%20previously%20stopped%20them%20from%20commuting%20to%20the%20office%2C%20they%20now%20feel%20they%20can%20log%20on%20from%20home%20and%20work%20through%20their%20symptoms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Roughly%20ten%20passengers%20sit%20in%20the%20carriage%20of%20a%20London%20tube.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d06b7643b5e59d16b65de2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHybrid%20workers%20feel%20pressure%20to%20be%20seen%20as%20reliable.%3Cp%3ENurPhoto%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20an%20advantage%20for%20minor%20ailments%20where%20you%20can%20answer%20a%20few%20emails%20and%20avoid%20falling%20behind%2C%20but%20where%20serious%20mental%20health%20concerns%20or%20exhaustion%20from%20illness%20builds%20up%2C%20the%20autonomy%20that%20hybrid%20work%20provides%20workers%20is%20detrimental%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20very%20poorly%2C%20I%20don't%20think%20people%20should%20be%20working.%20Even%20if%20they%20can%20do%20a%20few%20emails%20here%20and%20there%2C%20you%20really%20need%20recuperation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2225ad47fe-a582-4d1f-b99f-f82ce8a1f008%5C%22%3EHow%20to%20treat%20a%20sick%20employee%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20some%20evidence%20suggests%20US%20workers%20are%20taking%20more%20sick%20days%2C%20they%20are%20hardly%20becoming%20slackers%20%E2%80%94%20a%202023%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2023%2F08%2F10%2Fmore-than-4-in-10-u-s-workers-dont-take-all-their-paid-time-off%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPew%20Research%3C%2Fa%3E%20survey%20of%20nearly%206%2C000%20workers%20who%20are%20offered%20PTO%20found%20that%2046%25%20didn't%20take%20all%20that%20was%20owed%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20Dooley%20and%20Cooper%20said%20that%20the%20responsibility%20for%20finding%20a%20balance%20around%20sick%20leave%20lies%20with%20managers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTrue%20leaders%20grasp%20that%20in%20terms%20of%20productivity%2C%20it's%20better%20in%20the%20long%20term%20to%20allow%20people%20that%20time%20for%20their%20well-being%20over%20short-term%20productivity%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dooley.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20issue%20here%2C%20Cooper%20pointed%20out%2C%20is%20that%20people%20are%20promoted%20to%20managerial%20roles%20based%20on%20their%20technical%20skills%2C%20not%20their%20people%20skills.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20old%20euphemism%20applies%3A%20people%20don't%20leave%20a%20job%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhen-to-quit-your-job-for-new-boss-career-growth-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethey%20leave%20a%20boss%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Somebody%20with%20good%20emotional%20intelligence%2C%20who%20has%20got%20social%20and%20interpersonal%20skills%2C%20would%20say%2C%20'Oh%2C%20just%20take%20the%20day%20off.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20that's%20not%20a%20boss's%20natural%20tendency%20or%20their%20priority%20is%20meeting%20quarterly%20targets%20rather%20than%20the%20team's%20welfare%2C%20then%20executives%20should%20emphasize%20that%20keeping%20people%20engaged%20and%20feeling%20valued%20is%20more%20important.%20If%20that's%20not%20happening%2C%20then%20raise%20it%20in%20your%20performance%20review%2C%20he%20advised.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20legislation%20is%20also%20forcing%20the%20issue%20in%20some%20states.%20In%20January%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-new-laws-abortion-lgbtq-marijuana-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECalifornia%3C%2Fa%3E%20increased%20the%20minimum%20number%20of%20days%20of%20sick%20leave%20you%20can%20take%20from%20three%20to%20five%2C%20for%20example.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20fact%20that%20there%20are%20states%20that%20are%20doing%20that%20suggests%20to%20me%20that%20there's%20more%20to%20come%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dooley.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20an%20easy%20win%20for%20politicians.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsick-leave-more-complicated-in-hybrid-work-era-gen-z-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725794402000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66cd99d943b5e59d16b5780a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsick-leave-more-complicated-in-hybrid-work-era-gen-z-2024-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Americans%20and%20Brits%20take%20sick%20leave%20differently%20post-pandemic%3B%20HR%20experts%20discuss%20the%20impact%20of%20Gen%20Z%20attitudes%20and%20hybrid%20work%20on%20sick%20leave%20trends.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22pthompson%40insider.com%20(Polly%20Thompson)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsick-leave-more-complicated-in-hybrid-work-era-gen-z-2024-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22When%20Ash%20said%20that%20she%20and%20Abhishek%20fight%20daily%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725794133000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-113073625%2Cimgsize-41522.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fwhen-aishwarya-rai-bachchan-confessed-that-she-and-abhishek-bachchan-fight-every-day-it-would-be-really-boring-%2Farticleshow%2F113073626.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F113073626.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EAbhi