0tall%2C%20she's%20tiny%2C%20blond%2C%20and%20freakishly%20fit.%20She's%20also%2C%20perhaps%2C%20the%20peppiest%20person%20I've%20ever%20met%20%E2%80%94%20the%20kind%20of%20energizer%20bunny%20perfect%20for%20rallying%20a%20yet-to-be-caffeinated%20audience%20at%209%20in%20the%20morning.%20So%2C%20like%20any%20good%20motivational%20speaker%2C%20she%20starts%20with%20a%20joke.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20want%20to%20say%3A%20%3Cem%3EDrink%20the%20Kool-Aid%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20announces.%20%26quot%3BBut%20the%20people%20who%20drank%20the%20Kool-Aid%20died.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20room%20erupts%20in%20laughter.%20To%20be%20clear%2C%20it's%20not%20an%20easy%20room.%20Erin%20is%20addressing%2050%20women%2C%20every%20one%20of%20them%20a%20titan%20of%20industry%20%E2%80%94%20founders%2C%20CEOs%2C%20every%20iteration%20of%20%26quot%3Bvice%20president%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bdirector%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bpartner%26quot%3B%20you%20can%20possibly%20imagine.%20They%20have%20neither%20the%20time%20nor%20the%20patience%20for%20bullshit.%20They%20aren't%20here%20for%20some%20two-bit%20pep%20talk.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThey're%20here%20because%20after%20years%20of%20killing%20it%20in%20their%20hyper-elite%20careers%2C%20they%20had%20finally%20made%20it%20to%20the%20top%20of%20the%20corporate%20ladder%2C%20only%20to%20discover%20that%20the%20climb%20had%20made%20them%20miserable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20were%20crying%20every%20day.%20They%20were%20exhausted%2C%20irritable%2C%20apathetic%20%E2%80%94%20their%20burnout%20so%20bad%2C%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20that%20they%20had%20to%20go%20on%20medical%20leave.%20There%20was%20an%20emptiness%20to%20their%20lives%2C%20a%20nagging%20is-this-all-there-is-to-life%20feeling%20they%20could%20no%20longer%20suppress.%20They%20knew%20they%20should%20work%20less%2C%20but%20being%20an%20ultra-high-performer%20is%20who%20they%20%3Cem%3Eare%3C%2Fem%3E.%20In%20a%20world%20that%20requires%20them%20to%20do%20twice%20as%20much%20as%20men%20to%20get%20half%20the%20credit%2C%20how%20could%20they%20afford%20to%20slow%20down%3F%20These%20women%20aren't%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foverachievers-leaning-back-hustle-culture-coasting-employees-work%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Equiet%20quitters%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They're%20the%20people%20who%20%3Cem%3Efire%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethe%20quiet%20quitters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20they%20decided%20to%20see%20whether%20they%20could%20solve%20the%20problem%20with%20something%20they%20have%20plenty%20of%3A%20money.%20For%20the%20privilege%20of%20attending%20this%20life-coaching%20retreat%20for%20female%20executives%20and%20senior%20managers%2C%20they%20first%20had%20to%20complete%20an%20eight-week%2C%20%2416%2C000%20introductory%20course%20over%20Zoom%20called%20Corporate%20Women%20Unleashed%2C%20after%20which%20most%20of%20them%20enrolled%20in%20a%20%241%2C500-a-month%20advanced%20class%2C%20also%20over%20Zoom.%20Many%20are%20deeply%20devoted%20to%20the%20program%3B%20for%20one%20woman%2C%20a%20recently%20retired%20executive%20at%20a%20very%20large%20tech%20company%2C%20this%20is%20her%20sixth%20retreat.%20Erin%20needn't%20have%20bothered%20with%20her%20opening%20joke.%20These%20women%20didn't%20just%20drink%20the%20Kool-Aid.%20They've%20been%20guzzling%20it%20for%20months%2C%20if%20not%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EErin%20asks%20us%20to%20join%20her%20in%20chanting%20a%20mantra%20of%20sorts%2C%20to%20set%20our%20intention%20for%20the%20weekend.%20%26quot%3BI%20vow%20to%20challenge%20the%20status%20quo%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20begins.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%26quot%3BI%20vow%20to%20challenge%20the%20status%20quo%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%20everyone%20repeats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20make%20the%20glass%20ceiling%20my%20floor%2C%26quot%3B%20Erin%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%26quot%3BTo%20make%20the%20glass%20ceiling%20my%20floor.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20put%20my%20magic%20into%20the%20world%20courageously%2C%26quot%3B%20Erin%20continues.%20%26quot%3BTo%20use%20naysayers%20as%20gasoline%20for%20my%20fire.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20squirm%20in%20my%20seat.%20%3Cem%3ENo%20man%20would%20be%20caught%20dead%20saying%20this%20stuff%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20I%20think.%20But%20the%20women%20in%20the%20room%20all%20look%20stone-cold%20serious.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20theme%20of%20the%20retreat%20is%20%26quot%3B10x%2C%26quot%3B%20loosely%20based%20on%20a%20self-help%20book%20with%20the%20mathematically%20questionable%20title%20%26quot%3B10x%20Is%20Easier%20Than%202x.%26quot%3B%20According%20to%20the%20book's%20website%2C%2010x%20refers%20to%20%26quot%3Bexponential%20growth.%26quot%3B%20Erin%20asks%20everyone%20to%20share%20why%20they're%20here%20this%20weekend.%20She%20points%20to%20someone%20in%20the%20front.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20need%20to%20feel%20that%20I%20belong%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20woman%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWow%2C%26quot%3B%20Erin%20says%20as%20everyone%20claps.%20%26quot%3BIt%20speaks%20to%20what%20it%20means%20to%20be%20a%20woman%20at%20the%20top.%20It%20can%20be%20lonely.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20senior%20manager%20of%20communications%20takes%20the%20mic.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20here%20to%2010x%20my%20confidence%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says%2C%20her%20declaration%20so%20tentative%20she%20offers%20it%20more%20like%20a%20question.%20She's%20tearing%20up.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20to%20be%20able%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20to%2010x%20where%20I'm%20at%20today%20without%20giving%20up%20on%2010x-ing%20what's%20next.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20room%20claps%20again%2C%20and%20more%20women%20chime%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20whole%20life%20has%20always%20been%20about%20my%20career.%20I%20feel%20like%20there's%20something%20more.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20here%20because%20I%20sold%20my%20company%20last%20year.%20I'm%20making%20my%20exit%20now%20and%20I%20don't%20know%20what%20life%20looks%20like%20next.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20want%20to%2010x%20my%20badassery.%20I'm%20a%20badass%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20own%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20women%20testify%2C%20Kathleen%20Byars%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20the%20program%2C%20stands%20quietly%20to%20the%20side%20%E2%80%94%20smiling%2C%20clapping%2C%20delivering%20mics%20to%20people%20across%20the%20room.%20But%20after%20a%20while%2C%20she%20announces%20that%20she%20wants%20to%20weigh%20in.%20A%20hushed%20silence%20sets%20in.%20The%20women%20worship%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20so%20normalized%20in%20this%20room%20that%20we%20do%20big%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Byars.%20%26quot%3BWe%20do%20them%20quickly%2C%20we%20do%20them%20fast%2C%20and%20we%20want%20it.%20There's%20nobody%20here%20saying%3A%20'You're%20a%20little%20bit%20too%20intense.%20Can't%20you%20just%20be%20happy%20with%20what%20you%20have%3F%20Just%20%3Cem%3Erelax%3C%2Fem%3E.'%26quot%3B%20Several%20women%20nod%20emphatically.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEveryone%20here%20is%20like%2C%20'Yeahhh!%20Yeahhh!'%26quot%3B%20Byars%20continues.%20%26quot%3BJust%20think%20about%20that.%20That's%20rare.%20I%20can't%20tell%20you%20how%20many%20rooms%20I've%20been%20in%20where%20people%20say%2C%20'Kate%2C%20you%20just%20need%20to%20settle%20down.'%20You%20do%20%3Cem%3Enot%3C%2Fem%3E%20need%20to%20settle%20down.%20So%20thank%20you.%26quot%3B%20The%20room%20erupts%20in%20applause.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20the%20desire%20to%20reorient%20one's%20relationship%20to%20work%20is%20familiar%20to%20millions%20of%20Americans.%20But%20for%20few%20has%20its%20pursuit%20been%20more%20complicated%20than%20for%20the%20elite%20career%20women%20Byars%20strives%20to%20help.%20They%20have%20exceptionally%20demanding%20jobs%2C%20and%20equally%20demanding%20lives%20at%20home.%20Stepping%20away%20from%20their%20careers%20doesn't%20strike%20them%20as%20a%20desirable%20option%2C%20but%20there%20are%20only%20so%20many%20hours%20in%20a%20day.%20If%20they%20don't%20cut%20back%20on%20work%2C%20how%20can%20they%20hope%20to%20achieve%20a%20better%20work-life%20balance%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EByars%20says%20there's%20a%20better%20way.%20It's%20possible%2C%20she%20promises%2C%20to%20achieve%20personal%20fulfillment%20%3Cem%3Eat%20the%20same%20time%20as%3C%2Fem%3E%20professional%20success.%20You%20don't%20have%20to%20choose.%20She%20has%20let%20me%20attend%20this%20retreat%20in%20Nashville%2C%20and%20the%20eight-week%20Zoom%20intensive%20that%20preceded%20it%2C%20on%20the%20condition%20I%20don't%20name%20any%20of%20her%20clients.%20I'm%20here%20because%20I%20want%20to%20see%20whether%20her%20method%20works%20%E2%80%94%20not%20only%20for%20these%20women%20but%20also%2C%20maybe%20a%20little%20bit%2C%20for%20myself.%20Mostly%20I'm%20just%20curious%20to%20get%20a%20rare%20peek%20behind%20the%20retreat's%20gilded%20closed%20doors%20into%20the%20minds%20and%20souls%20of%20the%20most%20powerful%20women%20in%20American%20business.%20In%20this%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhustle-culture-got-america-addicted-to-work%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epost-hustle%20culture%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20post-%26quot%3BLean%20In%26quot%3B%20age%2C%20what%20does%20it%20mean%20to%20be%20a%20woman%20and%20a%20boss%20who%20still%20wants%20it%20all%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EByars%2C%2054%2C%20was%20once%20an%20overworked%20and%20unhappy%20corporate%20executive%20herself.%20By%20the%20time%20she%20was%2030%2C%20she%20was%20the%20international%20vice%20president%20of%20marketing%20at%20the%20cosmetics%20giant%20Mary%20Kay.%20She%20was%20flying%20first%20class%20around%20the%20world.%20She%20had%20a%20driver%2C%20a%20housekeeper%2C%20and%20a%20personal%20shopper.%20She%20was%20killing%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20life%20was%20also%20killing%20her.%20At%2033%2C%20when%20she%20lost%20her%20job%20in%20a%20management%20shake-up%2C%20Byars%20could%20have%20had%20her%20pick%20of%20any%20number%20of%20executive%20gigs.%20But%20she%20was%20so%20exhausted%20she%20couldn't%20imagine%20taking%20another%20job.%20She%20sold%20pretty%20much%20everything%20she%20owned%2C%20including%20her%203%2C000-square-foot%20home%20in%20Dallas%2C%20and%20moved%20to%20the%20Virgin%20Islands%20with%20her%20then-boyfriend%2C%20Scott.%20%26quot%3BI%20did%20what%20everybody%20else%20says%20to%20do%3A%20Live%20the%20simple%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20going%20to%20be%20a%20dive%20bum.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222850%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20sitting%20at%20a%20desk%20made%20out%20of%20a%20vise%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66c4fcc8b4912df3ae1d1d20%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222250%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFemale%20executives%20feel%20especially%20trapped%20between%20the%20demands%20of%20career%20and%20home.%20If%20they%20don't%20cut%20back%20on%20work%2C%20how%20can%20they%20hope%20to%20achieve%20a%20better%20work-life%20balance%3F%3Cp%3EKiersten%20Essenpreis%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20simple%20life%20worked%20for%20her%20for%20six%20glorious%20weeks.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20then%20I%20realized%3A%20Oh%20shit%2C%20I've%20just%20given%20up%20everything%20I've%20spent%20the%20last%2020%20years%20building%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20recalls.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%26quot%3BI%20cried%20for%20four%20months%20straight.%20I%20was%20just%20devastated.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20she%20finally%20felt%20ready%20to%20go%20back%20to%20corporate%20life%2C%20she%20looked%20for%20a%20more%20sustainable%20way%20to%20pursue%20professional%20success.%20She%20experimented%20with%20different%20strategies%20for%20achieving%20work-life%20balance%2C%20while%20Scott%2C%20an%20amateur%20philosopher%20and%20psychology%20geek%2C%20read%20everything%20he%20could%20on%20the%20subject.%20After%20years%20of%20trial%20and%20error%2C%20they%20finally%20got%20to%20a%20place%20where%20Byars%20was%20thriving%20both%20at%20work%20and%20at%20home%20with%20Scott%20and%20their%20two%20young%20sons.%20But%20her%20newfound%20insight%20had%20come%20at%20a%20steep%20cost%3A%20She%20estimated%20it%20had%20required%20her%20to%20forgo%20some%20%242%20million%20in%20earnings.%20Could%20she%20help%20other%20women%20get%20to%20the%20nirvana%20she%20attained%2C%20without%20all%20the%20messiness%20in%20the%20middle%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20find%20out%2C%20Byars%20founded%20The%20Goodlife%20Institute%20in%202017.%20The%20program's%20framework%20is%20founded%20on%20what%20she%20calls%20%26quot%3Bour%20seven%20universal%20needs%26quot%3B%3A%20autonomy%2C%20security%2C%20health%2C%20leisure%2C%20purpose%2C%20connection%2C%20and%20esteem.%20%26quot%3BThese%20seven%20needs%20are%20how%20human%20beings%20have%20biologically%20and%20psychologically%20evolved%20in%20order%20to%20survive%20and%20thrive%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says%20in%20the%20first%20of%20the%20Week%20One%20videos%20I%20received%20for%20Corporate%20Women%20Unleashed.%20%26quot%3BAll%20seven%20of%20them%20have%20to%20be%20met%20in%20order%20for%20you%20to%20experience%20optimal%20well-being.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20issue%20with%20high-achieving%20women%2C%20Byars%20says%2C%20is%20they%20focus%20on%20meeting%20only%20two%20of%20those%20needs%20%E2%80%94%20security%20(money)%20and%20esteem%20%E2%80%94%20while%20neglecting%20the%20rest.%20As%20Byars%20sees%20it%2C%20unmet%20needs%20are%20what%20lead%20to%20unhappiness.%20Her%20solution%20is%20to%20figure%20out%20which%20needs%20you're%20neglecting%20entirely%2C%20along%20with%20which%20needs%20you're%20not%20meeting%20effectively.%20Then%20her%20program%20helps%20you%20devise%20and%20implement%20better%20strategies%20to%20consistently%20meet%20all%20your%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20videos%20assigned%20each%20week%20introduce%20the%20pillars%20of%20her%20philosophy.%20After%20reviewing%20them%2C%20clients%20have%20Zoom%20calls%20with%20Erin%20and%20Ali%2C%20the%20coaches%20Byars%20employs%2C%20to%20learn%20how%20to%20apply%20the%20principles%20in%20their%20own%20lives.%20Every%20client%20gets%20three%20one-on-one%20calls%20with%20a%20coach%2C%20but%20most%20of%20the%20work%20happens%20in%20small%20groups%2C%20where%20everyone%20shares%20their%20real-life%20struggles.%20It's%20group%20therapy%20meets%20executive%20coaching%2C%20for%20the%20world's%20most%20successful%20and%20hard-ass%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20the%20moments%20are%20incredibly%20raw.%20On%20one%20call%2C%20a%20high-ranking%20government%20official%20confesses%20that%20she's%20been%20neglecting%20her%20family%20for%20months%20after%20a%20recent%20promotion.%20%26quot%3BI%20know%20it's%20having%20an%20effect%20on%20everybody%2C%20including%20me%2C%20and%20I'm%20trying%20to%20be%20better%20about%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BBut%20there's%20a%20big%20part%20of%20me%20that%20doesn't%20want%20to.%20I'm%20avoiding%20home.%26quot%3B%20The%20previous%20day%20she%20wrapped%20up%20her%20work%20at%20a%20reasonable%20time%2C%20but%20as%20she%20was%20driving%20home%20she%20saw%20a%20friend's%20car%20at%20a%20bar%20they%20frequent%20and%20decided%20to%20join%20her.%20She%20ended%20up%20staying%20for%20hours.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20so%20mad%20at%20myself%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20got%20home%20right%20before%20the%20kids%20went%20to%20bed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECould%20it%20be%2C%20Erin%20asks%2C%20that%20you%20were%20trying%20to%20meet%20your%20need%20for%20autonomy%20by%20hanging%20out%20with%20your%20friend%3F%20The%20woman%20nods%2C%20and%20several%20other%20women%20on%20the%20call%20nod%20in%20agreement.%20Raising%20kids%20is%20hard%20work%2C%20Erin%20observes%2C%20and%20there's%20no%20immediate%20payoff.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20in%20a%20very%20high-stress%20job%2C%20lots%20of%20demands%20on%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20Erin%20says.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20do%20you%20like%20doing%20with%20your%20kids%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNot%20a%20whole%20lot%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20official%20says.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20what%20I%20struggle%20with.%26quot%3B%20Her%20son%2C%20she%20notes%2C%20likes%20Godzilla.%20%26quot%3BI%20like%20to%20work.%26quot%3B%20It's%20the%20kind%20of%20admission%20that%20would%20seem%20unremarkable%20coming%20from%20a%20male%20executive.%20But%20the%20official%20felt%20guilt-ridden%20about%20it.%20%26quot%3BPaying%20more%20attention%20to%20their%20intrinsic%20interests%20is%20something%20I%20need%20to%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20hard%20for%20me%20because%2C%20I%20mean%2C%20I'll%20be%20honest%2C%20I'm%20a%20fairly%20self-centered%20person.%20And%20that's%20also%20contributing%20to%20this%20dynamic.%20So%20%E2%80%94%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSorry%2C%20I%20call%20bullshit%2C%26quot%3B%20Erin%20interjects.%20%26quot%3BThe%20role%20you're%20in%20is%20not%20a%20self-centered%20role.%20You%20are%20giving%2C%20giving%2C%20giving%2C%20changing%2C%20changing%2C%20changing.%20In%20the%20home%20world%2C%20you're%20like%2C%20I%20can't%20do%20it%20anymore.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20resonates%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20woman%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20have%20a%20lot%20left%20to%20give%20at%20home%20and%20I%20need%20to%20shift%20that%20so%20I%20do.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EErin%20probes%20further.%20You're%20in%20this%20deficit%20where%20you%20have%20nothing%20left%20to%20give%2C%20she%20says%2C%20so%20let's%20focus%20on%20%3Cem%3Eyou%20%3C%2Fem%3Efirst.%20Let's%20meet%20your%20need%20for%20leisure.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20did%20you%20like%20to%20do%20as%20a%20kid%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20mean%2C%20I%20worked%20all%20the%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20official%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20did%20school.%20I%20was%20great%20at%20school.%20I%20got%20a%20job%20the%20minute%20I%20could%20get%20a%20job.%20I%20have%20not%20prioritized%20fun%20in%20my%20life%2C%20ever.%20Ever.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EErin%20asks%20her%20to%20commit%20to%20one%20thing%20she'll%20do%20for%20herself%20over%20the%20weekend.%20Sleep%2C%20the%20official%20says.%20Perhaps%20that%20will%20help%20her%20feel%20less%20depleted%20at%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20the%20kind%20of%20reframing%20that%20happens%20all%20the%20time%20in%20therapy.%20But%20this%20is%20different%2C%20because%20these%20women%20are%20also%20getting%20validation%20from%20their%20peers.%20Two%20of%20them%2C%20both%20mothers%2C%20chime%20in%20to%20thank%20the%20official%20for%20being%20so%20candid.%20%26quot%3BI%20have%20the%20exact%20same%20guilt%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20doctor%20with%20her%20own%20practice%20says.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20not%20alone%20in%20that.%26quot%3B%20Another%20woman%20cries%2C%20sharing%20how%20she%20struggled%20with%20a%20similar%20dilemma%20until%20her%20son%20developed%20an%20eating%20disorder%20so%20serious%20that%20he%20had%20to%20enter%20residential%20treatment.%20%26quot%3BIt%20honestly%20took%20me%20losing%20my%20son%20in%20the%20short%20term%20%E2%80%94%20thankfully%20I%20got%20him%20back%20%E2%80%94%20to%20prioritize%20and%20realize%20what%20I%20had.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20the%20crying%3A%20There%20was%20a%20%3Cem%3Elot%20%3C%2Fem%3Eof%20it.%20I'm%20not%20sure%20I%20was%20on%20a%20single%20call%20where%20no%20one%20cried.%20And%20these%20are%20hardened%20executives%2C%20who%20climbed%20to%20where%20they%20are%20by%20being%20just%20as%20stoic%20and%20emotionally%20repressed%20as%20the%20men%20around%20them.%20They're%20not%2C%20as%20several%20of%20them%20insisted%20to%20me%2C%20the%20kumbaya%20crying-in-group-therapy%20type.%20(Or%20even%20the%20crying-in-individual-therapy%20type%20%E2%80%94%20one%20told%20me%20she%20found%20therapy%20%26quot%3Btoo%20fluffy.%26quot%3B)%20As%20one%20client%20said%2C%20if%20you%20had%20told%20her%20she%20was%20going%20to%20share%20her%20deepest%20feelings%20with%20a%20group%20of%20strangers%20who%20would%20rally%20around%20and%20support%20her%20while%20she%20broke%20down%20in%20tears%2C%20her%20response%20would%20have%20been%3A%20%26quot%3BAre%20you%20fucking%20kidding%20me%3F%20%3Cem%3ENo%3C%2Fem%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20clients%20cry%2C%20it's%20mostly%20related%20to%20the%20need%20Byars%20says%20is%20the%20trickiest%20to%20meet%3A%20esteem.%20High-achieving%20women%20try%20to%20fill%20it%2C%20she%20says%2C%20by%20accomplishing%20an%20ever-more-impressive%20list%20of%20things.%20But%20when%20they're%20not%20accomplishing%2C%20their%20self-esteem%20disintegrates%2C%20creating%20a%20seemingly%20unbreakable%20cycle%20of%20overwork%20and%20burnout.%20Byars%20seeks%20to%20help%20female%20executives%20develop%20a%20new%20belief%20%E2%80%94%20that%20they're%20valuable%20for%20who%20they%20are%2C%20not%20what%20they%20do.%20And%20the%20way%20she%20gets%20them%20to%20develop%20that%20belief%20is%20through%20an%20exercise%20she%20calls%20an%20%26quot%3Bemotional%20elevator.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20might%20more%20accurately%20be%20referred%20to%20as%20%26quot%3Bemotional%20waterboarding.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20every%20Zoom%20call%2C%20there's%20a%20room%20devoted%20to%20emotional%20elevators.%20In%20that%20room%2C%20the%20coach%20interrogates%20reluctant%20volunteers%20about%20their%20feelings.%20Every%20time%20a%20woman%20describes%20a%20feeling%2C%20the%20coach%20pushes%20them%20to%20go%20deeper%20by%20asking%20them%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20are%20you%20making%20that%20mean%3F%26quot%3B%20The%20coach%20does%20this%20over%20and%20over%20and%20over%20again.%20Eventually%20the%20poor%20executive%20is%20reduced%20to%20sobbing%2C%20whimpering%20something%20along%20the%20lines%20of%20%3Cem%3EI'm%20not%20good%20enough%20%3C%2Fem%3Ein%20front%20of%20the%20whole%20group.%20From%20there%2C%20the%20coach%20guides%20the%20client%20to%20develop%20a%20new%20belief%20about%20themselves%20by%20asking%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20else%20could%20be%20true%3F%26quot%3B%20The%20goal%20is%20for%20the%20women%20to%20supply%20their%20confidence%20from%20within%20themselves%2C%20instead%20of%20seeking%20evidence%20of%20their%20value%20from%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223084%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20crying%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66c4fd031aa2ac29ee32ae3e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222344%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAbout%20the%20crying%3A%20There%20was%20a%20lot%20of%20it.%20I'm%20not%20sure%20I%20was%20on%20a%20single%20Zoom%20call%20where%20no%20one%20cried.%20And%20these%20are%20hardened%20executives%2C%20not%20the%20kumbaya%20crying-in-group-therapy%20type.%20%3Cp%3EKiersten%20Essenpreis%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20elevators%20are%20uncomfortable%20to%20watch%2C%20and%20impossible%20not%20to%20find%20deeply%20moving.%20On%20one%20call%2C%20a%20partner%20at%20a%20law%20firm%20talks%20through%20why%20she%20feels%20so%20upset%20that%20one%20of%20her%20junior%20lawyers%20just%20left%2C%20even%20after%20all%20the%20training%20and%20mentoring%20she%20provided.%20(Her%20belief%3A%20She%20wasn't%20good%20enough%20for%20them%20to%20want%20to%20stay.)%20On%20another%20call%2C%20a%20young%20tech%20manager%20explores%20why%20she%20doesn't%20think%20she'll%20get%20a%20job%20other%20colleagues%20think%20she'll%20be%20a%20shoo-in%20for.%20(Her%20belief%3A%20She%20isn't%20good%20enough%20for%20the%20new%20job%2C%20or%20even%20her%20current%20one.)%20I%20sniffled%20through%20the%20process%20three%20times%20myself%20%E2%80%94%20once%20over%20the%20panic%20I%20feel%20before%20writing%20a%20big%20story%20(this%20is%20the%20time%20everyone%20will%20realize%20I'm%20a%20bad%20writer)%2C%20once%20over%20my%20anxiety%20at%20being%20in%20a%20profession%20beset%20by%20unrelenting%20layoffs%20(I'll%20never%20find%20another%20occupation%20I%20like%20this%20much)%2C%20and%20once%20over%20the%20time%20I%20sensed%20I%20was%20about%20to%20get%20dumped%20by%20someone%20I%20was%20dating%20(I'm%20not%20attractive%20and%20I'll%20die%20alone).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThrough%20all%20the%20tears%2C%20though%2C%20I%20watched%20my%20cohort%20make%20real%20progress.%20One%20weekend%2C%20when%20a%20bunch%20of%20things%20at%20her%20law%20firm%20blew%20up%2C%20the%20partner%20delegated%20the%20fires%20to%20her%20underlings%20instead%20of%20handling%20them%20on%20her%20own.%20The%20doctor%20who%20felt%20guilty%20about%20not%20spending%20time%20with%20her%20kids%20booked%20a%20trip%20to%20go%20see%20the%20eclipse%20with%20them.%20The%20tech%20manager%20landed%20a%20new%20job%20at%20her%20company%2C%20to%20get%20away%20from%20difficult%20colleagues.%20A%20CEO%20battling%20a%20toxic%20board%20finally%20stood%20up%20for%20herself%20and%20stepped%20down.%20She%20no%20longer%20looks%20to%20her%20job%20%26quot%3Bfor%20validation%20as%20a%20human%20being%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BI%20know%20my%20worth%20better%20than%20before.%20I%20deserve%20to%20be%20treated%20differently.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20another%20CEO%20started%20prioritizing%20her%20own%20well%20being%2C%20her%20husband%20noticed%20something%20different%20about%20her.%20%26quot%3BMan%2C%20you%20look%20good%20to%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20her.%20The%20CEO%20laughs%20as%20she%20shares%20this%20with%20the%20group%2C%20blushing%20as%20if%20she's%20talking%20about%20a%20teenage%20crush.%20In%20fact%2C%20she%20%3Cem%3Edoes%3C%2Fem%3E%20look%20different%20than%20she%20did%20at%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20program%20%E2%80%94%20color%20back%20in%20her%20cheeks%2C%20less%20depleted%2C%20her%20hair%20fuller.%20So%20do%20several%20of%20the%20other%20women.%20They%20speak%20less%20frantically.%20They%20smile%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20even%20noticed%20a%20change%20in%20myself.%20As%20I%20went%20about%20my%20life%2C%20saying%20yes%20to%20too%20many%20things%2C%20writing%20until%20midnight%2C%20second-guessing%20everything%20I%20said%20on%20a%20date%2C%20I%20started%20to%20hear%20Erin's%20words%20in%20my%20head.%20What%20need%20was%20I%20trying%20to%20meet%3F%20Was%20that%20really%20the%20best%20strategy%20to%20meet%20that%20need%3F%20What%20strategy%20could%20I%20use%20next%20time%3F%20My%20sister%2C%20who%20knows%20me%20better%20than%20anyone%2C%20told%20me%20she%20saw%20a%20subtle%20shift%20in%20me.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20talking%20about%20things%20a%20little%20differently%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20my%20surprise%2C%20I'm%20sad%20when%20the%20eight%20weeks%20are%20over.%20But%20next%20up%20is%20the%20retreat%20in%20Nashville.%20It%20feels%20like%20being%20called%20up%20to%20the%20big%20leagues.%20The%20executives%20attending%20the%20event%20have%20already%20finished%20Corporate%20Women%20Unleashed%20and%20have%20moved%20on%20to%20the%20advanced%20program%2C%20which%20has%20a%20name%20suited%20to%20its%20power-broker%20clientele%3A%20Optimum.%20They've%20been%20having%20monthly%20one-on-one%20calls%20with%20their%20coach%2C%20and%20meeting%20regularly%20over%20Zoom%20in%20small%20cohorts.%20Now%20it's%20all%20culminating%20with%20a%20weekend-long%20event%20%E2%80%94%20the%20first%20time%20many%20of%20the%20women%20meet%20in%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20retreat%20kicks%20off%20on%20a%20balmy%2C%20bright%20afternoon%20at%20the%20hotel's%20rooftop%20pool.%20The%20women%20at%20the%20pool%20are%20gravitating%20to%20their%20cohorts.%20A%20senior%20manager%20of%20communications%20tells%20me%20she%20signed%20up%20for%20CWU%20for%20the%20same%20reason%20everyone%20else%20did%3A%20because%20she%20was%20burned%20out.%20She%20was%20working%20constantly%2C%20gaining%20weight%2C%20and%20sick%20from%20exhaustion.%20But%20what%20pushed%20her%20over%20the%20edge%20was%20when%20her%205-year-old%20started%20having%20panic%20attacks%20when%20she%20began%20traveling%20more%20for%20work.%20%26quot%3BThat%20was%20the%20wake-up%20call%20for%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20saw%20him%20and%20I%20was%20like%2C%20I'm%20not%20doing%20this%20to%20him.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20course%20of%20the%20weekend%2C%20I%20ask%20everyone%20I%20meet%20to%20explain%20the%20secret%20to%20the%20change%20they've%20undergone%20through%20CWU%20and%20Optimum.%20Many%20of%20them%20tell%20me%20they%20have%20shifted%20their%20mindset.%20But%20if%20you're%20a%20woman%20with%20four%20kids%20and%20a%20senior-level%20corporate%20job%2C%20is%20there%20really%20%3Cem%3Eany%3C%2Fem%3E%20amount%20of%20mindset%20shifting%20you%20can%20do%20to%20avoid%20burnout%3F%20%26quot%3BAt%20home%20it's%20a%20grind%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20communication%20manager%20admits.%20But%20now%2C%20she%20says%2C%20whether%20it's%20a%20kid's%20temper%20tantrum%20or%20a%20crisis%20at%20work%2C%20the%20chaos%20doesn't%20get%20to%20her%20the%20way%20it%20once%20did.%20Her%20burnout%20is%20gone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20no%20one%20has%20changed%20more%20than%20an%20HR%20executive%20I%20chat%20with%20at%20the%20bar%20at%20the%20cocktail%20reception%20later%20that%20night.%20She%20joined%20CWU%20after%20burning%20out%20during%20the%20early%20months%20of%20COVID.%20What%20she%20expected%20to%20learn%20were%20tools%20for%20work-life%20balance%3A%20how%20to%20create%20boundaries%2C%20calendar%20management%2C%20that%20kind%20of%20thing.%20But%20what%20she%20ended%20up%20getting%2C%20she%20says%2C%20was%20so%20much%20more.%20She%20describes%20herself%20as%20a%20totally%20different%20person%20now.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20this%20hard-ass%20just%20talking%20about%20results.%20I%20was%20hard%20on%20people%20and%20had%20no%20empathy%2C%20no%20compassion.%26quot%3B%20She%20laughs%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20now%20have%20conversations%20about%20my%20%3Cem%3Esoul%3C%2Fem%3E.%26quot%3B%20She's%20currently%20interviewing%20for%20a%20role%20that%20would%20get%20her%20a%20seat%20in%20the%20C-suite%2C%20which%20is%20something%20she's%20wanted%20her%20entire%20career.%20I%20note%20that%20she%20sounds%20oddly%20relaxed%20about%20it.%20%26quot%3BI'd%20be%20good%20at%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BBut%20I%20don't%20need%20the%20job%2C%20because%20there%20are%205%2C000%20other%20things%20I%20could%20do.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20we%20talk%2C%20Byars%20strolls%20by%20in%20an%20emerald-green%20dress.%20It's%20like%20spotting%20a%20celebrity%20on%20the%20red%20carpet.%20Every%20woman%20here%20wants%20to%20say%20hello%20and%20hug%20her%20and%20hold%20her%20attention%20for%20as%20long%20as%20they%20can.%20%26quot%3BShe's%20%3Cem%3Eamazing%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20women%20tell%20me%20no%20fewer%20than%20a%20dozen%20times%20over%20the%20course%20of%20the%20weekend.%20%26quot%3BShe's%20a%20%3Cem%3Egenius%3C%2Fem%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20walking%20up%20a%20ladder%20made%20out%20of%20hands%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66c4fc1fb4912df3ae1d1c4d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EByars%20describes%20the%20concept%20of%2010x%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bquantum%20leap%26quot%3B%20that%20gets%20you%20results%20%26quot%3Bbeyond%20our%20wildest%20expectations.%26quot%3B%20That's%20what%20differentiates%20it%20from%202x%2C%20which%20is%20only%20a%20%26quot%3Blinear%20step%2C%26quot%3B%20doing%20more%20or%20less%20what%20you%20did%20before.%3Cp%3EKiersten%20Essenpreis%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20morning%20we%20get%20down%20to%20business.%20We're%20seated%20at%20eight%20tables%20in%20a%20large%20conference%20room.%20The%20average%20age%20looks%20to%20be%20somewhere%20in%20the%20late%2040s.%20There%20are%20a%20smattering%20of%20doctors%20and%20veterinarians%2C%20a%20top%20hospital%20administrator%2C%20a%20senior%20engineer%20at%20a%20big%20oil%20company%2C%20and%20several%20founders%20and%20CEOs%20of%20small%20firms.%20The%20rest%20have%20titles%20that%20are%20a%20testament%20to%20the%20sprawling%20bureaucracy%20of%20modern%20American%20corporations%2C%20many%20of%20which%20are%20household%20names.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EByars%20begins%20by%20explaining%20the%20concept%20of%2010x.%20She%20describes%20it%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bquantum%20leap%26quot%3B%20that%20gets%20you%20results%20%26quot%3Bbeyond%20our%20wildest%20expectations.%26quot%3B%20That's%20what%20differentiates%20it%20from%202x%2C%20which%20is%20only%20a%20%26quot%3Blinear%20step%2C%26quot%3B%20doing%20more%20or%20less%20what%20you%20did%20before.%20It's%20all%20a%20bit%20murky%2C%20but%20for%20the%20purposes%20of%20the%20weekend%2C%20I%20understand%2010x%20to%20represent%20something%20really%2C%20really%20big%20that%20you%20really%2C%20really%20want%2C%20but%20that%20feels%20utterly%20impossible%20to%20achieve.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EByars%20talks%20about%20the%20two%20times%20she%20has%2010x'd%20her%20own%20life.%20The%20first%20was%20when%20she%20landed%20a%20senior-level%20job%20at%20Mary%20Kay%2C%20despite%20a%20total%20lack%20of%20experience.%20She%20did%20it%20by%20calling%20the%20hiring%20manager%20every%20week%20for%20six%20weeks%2C%20leaving%2045-minute%20unsolicited%20voicemails%20with%20her%20ideas%20about%20the%20job%20until%20they%20eventually%20gave%20it%20to%20her.%20The%20second%20was%20when%20she%20went%20searching%20for%20a%20husband.%20She%20looked%20everywhere%3A%20ladies'%20night%20at%20a%20bar%20frequented%20by%20doctors%20and%20lawyers%2C%20an%20opera%20club%20for%20young%20professionals%2C%20Habitat%20for%20Humanity.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20on%20a%20mission%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20Eventually%20she%20met%20Scott%20at%20a%20diving%20trip%20off%20the%20coast%20of%20Chile.%20But%20he%20was%20partnered%20with%20someone%20else%2C%20which%20required%20her%20to%20wait%20a%20long%20time%20for%20that%20relationship%20to%20come%20to%20an%20end.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20so%20improbable%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bthat%20five%20years%20later%20we%20were%20married.%26quot%3B%20Everyone%20in%20the%20room%20is%20furiously%20taking%20notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EByars%20asks%20us%20to%20come%20up%20with%20our%20own%2010x%20goal.%20Think%20about%20it%2C%20she%20says.%20What%20do%20you%20want%20in%2010%20years%3F%20Then%20think%20about%20it%20again%3A%20Is%20that%20what%20you%20%3Cem%3Ereally%3C%2Fem%3E%20want%2C%20or%20is%20that%20just%20what%20society%20wants%20you%20to%20want%3F%20What%20if%20you%20forget%20about%20whether%20it's%20socially%20acceptable%2C%20or%20even%20doable%3F%20What%20if%20you%20could%20have%20anything%20%E2%80%94%20%3Cem%3Eanything%20%E2%80%94%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20the%20world%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20the%20women%20struggle%20to%20come%20up%20with%20something%20specific.%20Through%20their%20time%20in%20CWU%20and%20Optimum%2C%20they've%20already%20cut%20their%2090-hour%20weeks%20to%2040%20hours%2C%20stopped%20second-guessing%20themselves%2C%20and%20found%20genuine%20joy%20in%20their%20jobs.%20Given%20how%20overworked%20and%20unhappy%20they%20were%20before%2C%20these%20are%20miraculous%20achievements.%20What%20more%20could%20they%20possibly%20want%3F%20Just%20how%20big%20do%20they%20have%20to%20dream%3F%20The%20senior%20auditing%20director%20and%20engineering%20director%20at%20my%20table%20are%20stumped.%20Do%20they%20want%20to%20change%20careers%3F%20Do%20they%20want%20kids%3F%20They%20seem%20unsure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20have%20plenty%20of%20things%20I%20want.%20I've%20been%20noodling%20on%20an%20idea%20for%20a%20book%20since%20the%20end%20of%20last%20year.%20I%20would%20love%20to%20write%20that%20and%20for%20it%20to%20mean%20something%20to%20the%20people%20who%20read%20it.%20But%20if%20I'm%20honest%20with%20myself%2C%20what%20I%20%3Cem%3Ereally%3C%2Fem%3E%20want%20in%2010%20years%20is%20to%20be%20married%20to%20a%20great%20partner%20and%20to%20be%20raising%20kids%20with%20her.%20But%20it's%20hard%20to%20admit%20that%2C%20because%20it's%20also%20what%20I%20wish%20I%20had%20right%20now%2C%20and%20don't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Byars%20comes%20over%20to%20our%20table%20to%20check%20on%20us%2C%20I%20tell%20her%20that%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20declare%20a%20goal%20over%20which%20I%20have%20zero%20control.%20No%20amount%20of%20trying%20is%20going%20to%20make%20my%20future%20partner%20appear%20out%20of%20thin%20air.%20Believe%20me%2C%20I%20tell%20her%2C%20I've%20tried.%20Don't%20I%20just%20have%20to%20distract%20myself%20until%20the%20right%20person%20comes%20along%3F%20Otherwise%20I'm%20just%20setting%20myself%20up%20for%20disappointment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EByars%20tells%20me%20about%20the%20time%20she%20spent%20waiting%20for%20Scott%20to%20become%20available.%20It%20was%20brutal%2C%20she%20says%2C%20to%20be%20so%20sure%20he%20was%20the%20one%20and%20not%20be%20with%20him.%20She%20asks%3A%20Why%20do%20you%20keep%20saying%20that%20you%20have%20no%20control%20over%20meeting%20someone%20who's%20right%20for%20you%3F%20Could%20it%20be%20that%20you%20have%20more%20control%20than%20you%20think%3F%20As%20we%20chat%2C%20I%20get%20why%20the%20women%20like%20her%20so%20much.%20It's%20not%20just%20that%20she's%20confident%20and%20unapologetic%20and%20funny.%20In%20that%20moment%20I%20feel%20genuinely%20seen%20by%20her%3A%20She%20exudes%20a%20true%2C%20guru-like%20charisma%20that%20convinces%20you%20she%20can%20peer%20into%20your%20soul.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20afternoon%20is%20devoted%20to%20a%20series%20of%20activities%20designed%20to%20get%20us%20out%20of%20our%20comfort%20zones%20and%20embolden%20us%20to%20do%20the%20unthinkable.%20One%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bscavenger%20hunt%2C%26quot%3B%20where%20we're%20tasked%20with%20getting%20photos%20and%20videos%20of%20ourselves%20doing%20slightly%20embarrassing%20things%20in%20public.%20(Sample%20assignment%3A%20going%20up%20to%20a%20stranger%20and%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20like%20your%20britches.%26quot%3B)%20I%20find%20it%20all%20mildly%20annoying%2C%20but%20the%20women%20seem%20to%20be%20having%20a%20blast.%20Byars%20knows%20her%20audience%2C%20I%20realize.%20If%20you're%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20corporate%20food%20chain%2C%20you%20aren't%20exactly%20encouraged%20to%20make%20yourself%20look%20ridiculous%20in%20front%20of%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20morning%2C%20the%20coaches%20show%20us%20the%20photos%20and%20videos%20from%20the%20scavenger%20hunt.%20In%20one%2C%20the%20HR%20executive%20who%20described%20herself%20to%20me%20as%20a%20longtime%20hard-ass%20stands%20next%20to%20a%20gigantic%20statue%20of%20a%20microphone%20alongside%20a%20CEO%20and%20a%20neurologist%20and%20belts%20out%20LeAnn%20Rimes'%20%26quot%3BHow%20Do%20I%20Live.%26quot%3B%20The%20three%20of%20them%20are%20totally%20and%20stunningly%20off-pitch.%20The%20HR%20executive's%20eyes%20are%20closed%2C%20and%20she%20has%20a%20huge%20smile%20on%20her%20face.%20I%20think%20about%20the%20government%20official%20in%20my%20CWU%20cohort%20who%20confessed%20she%20had%20never%20prioritized%20fun%20in%20her%20life.%20Watching%20the%20video%2C%20the%20HR%20executive%20laughs%20along%20with%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20room.%20Her%20cheeks%20are%20bright%20red%2C%20and%20she%20fans%20herself%20with%20her%20hand%20long%20after%20the%20video%20is%20over%2C%20never%20once%20breaking%20her%20impeccable%20posture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20lunch%2C%20we%20break%20into%20three%20groups.%20In%20one%2C%20the%20women%20sit%20in%20a%20semicircle%20around%20Byars%2C%20peppering%20her%20with%20questions.%20A%20management%20consultant%20talks%20about%20how%20she's%20always%20wanted%20to%20start%20her%20own%20company.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20see%20myself%20as%20a%20CEO%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20see%20myself%20as%20a%20follower.%26quot%3B%20The%20HR%20executive%20brings%20up%20her%20own%20dilemma.%20If%20she%20stays%20in%20her%20corporate%20job%20for%20three%20more%20years%2C%20she'll%20be%20able%20to%20save%20enough%20money%20that%20she'll%20never%20need%20to%20work%20again.%20%26quot%3BBut%20my%20patience%20is%20zero%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BThe%20corporate%20bullshit%20is%20just%20sucking%20my%20soul.%20It's%20%3Cem%3Esucking%3C%2Fem